name: Easy Chicken Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked, drained spaghetti noodles'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chicken breasts, cooked and cubed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '2 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cubes', 'name': 'chicken bouillon'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Put cooked spaghetti noodles into 9x13-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top of spaghetti.. Bring condensed soup, water, butter, and bouillon to a boil in a medium saucepan. Pour soup mixture over pasta and chicken. Sprinkle Cheddar on top and press down a bit.. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes.

name: Leftover Turkey Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'uncooked spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅔', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped cooked turkey'}
steps: Gather all ingredients, preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and lightly grease a baking dish.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add spaghetti, and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente. Drain, and place in the prepared baking dish.. Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Stir in flour. Mix in chicken broth and milk. Cook and stir until the mixture comes to a boil. Stir in about 1 1/3 cups Parmesan cheese, and remove from heat.. Mix chicken broth mixture and turkey with spaghetti. Top with remaining cheese.. Bake 1 hour in the preheated oven, until surface is lightly browned.. Serve and enjoy!

name: Ham Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'quarts', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of mushroom soup'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced ham'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped pimento peppers'}
steps: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add spaghetti and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain (or use leftover pasta; see Cook's Note).. While pasta is cooking, melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Stir in onion; cook and stir until the onion has softened and turned translucent, about 5 minutes.. Stir in cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup water, and shredded cheese. Heat mixture until cheese melts, stirring often.. Mix in the ham, cooked and drained pasta, chopped pimento, and chopped parsley to saucepan; stir to combine. Cook until mixture is heated through, then serve.

name: Chicken Tetrazzini for a Crowd
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'spaghetti, broken into pieces'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed cream of mushroom soup'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded boiled chicken breast meat'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'sauteed mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4 ounce) jar', 'name': 'sliced pimento peppers, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'reserved chicken broth'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add uncooked spaghetti (broken into thirds) to the pot and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente. Drain and set aside.. In a large saucepan, heat soup over low heat. Add shredded cheese (reserve some for topping) and stir together. Then add the cooked shredded chicken, mushrooms, pimento peppers and cooked spaghetti and stir all together. Add enough of the reserved broth to make it 'sloppy' and mix all together.. Pour mixture into a 9x13 inch baking dish. Sprinkle reserved shredded cheese on top and bake in the preheated oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

name: Chicken Tetrazzini IV
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'spaghetti, broken into pieces'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sherry'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add spaghetti, and cook for 8 to 10 minutes, or until al dente; drain.. Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Stir in flour, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until smooth. Remove from heat, and gradually stir in chicken broth and cream.. Return to heat, and bring to a low boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Add sherry, then stir in cooked spaghetti, mushrooms, and chicken. Pour mixture into the prepared baking dish, and top with Parmesan cheese.. Bake 30 minutes in the preheated oven, until bubbly and lightly browned.

name: Chicken Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'margarine'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'celery salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain; transfer to a large bowl.. Melt margarine in a skillet over medium heat. Add onion; cook and stir until soft and translucent, 5 to 7 minutes. Stir into spaghetti along with chicken, evaporated milk, cream of chicken soup, 4 ounces Cheddar cheese, celery salt, salt, and black pepper; toss to combine. Transfer to prepared dish; sprinkle remaining 4 ounces Cheddar cheese over top.. Bake in the preheated oven until bubbling and cheese melted, about 45 minutes.

steps: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain and set aside.. Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. name: Baked Turkey Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': ''}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'white mushrooms, sliced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cubed leftover cooked turkey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'peas'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'egg noodles, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}
steps: Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms, onion, and celery and cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle flour over mushroom mixture and stir to coat.. Mix milk, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, and nutmeg into mushroom mixture. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cream cheese is melted and sauce is warmed through, 5 to 10 minutes. Add turkey and peas to sauce.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking dish. Set aside.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook egg noodles, stirring occasionally until cooked through but slightly firm, about 5 minutes. Drain. Mix noodles into turkey mixture and transfer to the prepared baking dish.. Melt and cool the remaining 3 tablespoons butter. Add Parmesan cheese, and bread crumbs and stir until crumbly. Sprinkle over noodle mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven until top is browned and sauce is bubbling, about 30 minutes.

name: Classic Chicken Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '', 'name': 'chicken tenderloins'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '', 'name': 'yellow bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'uncooked spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ground black pepper, to taste'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Swiss cheese'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese for topping (Optional)'}
steps: In a large nonstick skillet, sauté tenderloins. Salt and pepper, to taste. Add mushrooms, red bell peppers, yellow bell peppers, and cook until vegetables are tender.. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and set aside.. In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine and blend in flour. Gradually stir in chicken broth and half-and-half. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce begins to thicken. Add garlic salt and ground black pepper, to taste. Blend in Swiss and Parmesan cheeses and continue heating, stirring constantly, until cheeses melt.. Stir in chicken-vegetable mixture and heat thoroughly. Toss with cooked pasta and top with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

name: Turkey Tetrazzini a la Stouffer's
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'sliced fresh mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2 ⅔', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sherry wine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'angel hair pasta'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced cooked turkey'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Grease a casserole dish with 2 teaspoons of butter.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook angel hair in boiling water, occasionally stirring until cooked through but firm to the bite, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain.. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large pot over medium heat; cook and stir celery until it begins to soften, 1 minute. Stir mushrooms into celery; cook and stir until mushrooms are softened, 3 minutes more.. Remove vegetables from skillet; melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter and whisk flour into hot butter to make a paste. Slowly whisk chicken broth and bring to a simmer; reduce heat to low and cook, constantly whisking, until sauce is thickened. Mix in cream, sherry, salt, and white pepper.. Fold turkey, celery, and mushrooms into sauce; mix in angel hair pasta. Transfer mixture to the prepared casserole dish and sprinkle panko crumbs on top.. Bake in the preheated oven until sauce is bubbling and crumb topping has browned, about 30 minutes.

name: Chicken Tetrazzini I
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) cans', 'name': 'mushrooms, drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'boneless chicken breast halves, cooked'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) container', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Break spaghettini into 1 inch pieces. Cook according to package directions. Drain.. Saute mushrooms in butter or margarine. Cut chicken into large pieces, and mix with mushrooms. Stir in sour cream and condensed soup. Fold in noodles. Turn into a buttered casserole dish, and sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.. Bake at 300 degrees F (150 degrees C) for 40 minutes.

name: Artichoke Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'linguini pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(6 ounce) can', 'name': 'marinated artichoke hearts'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Cook linguini in a large pot of boiling salted water until tender.. Meanwhile, saute mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine with thyme. Remove from heat. Stir in flour. Then stir in chicken broth and half and half. Return to heat, and stir until the sauce boils and thickens. Strain artichokes, and stir the liquid into the sauce. Add the fresh Parmesan.. Drain linguini, and toss with sauce. Fold in the strained artichokes. Serve immediately.

name: Chicken Tetrazzini II
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breast halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'stalk', 'name': 'celery'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'processed cheese food (eg. Velveeta)'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dry sherry'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornflakes cereal'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': '(12 ounce) package', 'name': 'egg noodles, cooked and drained'}
steps: Boil chicken breasts and celery in 4 cups of water for about 30 minutes. Remove from heat and remove chicken from water to cool. When chicken is cooled, shred and set aside.. In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid, and add to skillet. Heat thoroughly, seasoning with salt and pepper. Add evaporated milk, reserved mushroom liquid and sherry, stirring well. Add cheese a few slices at a time until thoroughly melted and blended. Add shredded chicken and bring to a slow boil.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees (175 C). Grease a 9x13x2 glass baking dish. Put in noodles at about a 1 1/2 inch depth and pour chicken mixture over noodles. Stir to coat. Top with cornflake crumbs and paprika, cover dish and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover dish and bake for 5 more minutes. Serve warm.

name: Turkey Tetrazzini
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'angel hair pasta'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced onion'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground white pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'poultry seasoning'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded sharp Cheddar cheese, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped pimento peppers (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(4.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cooked turkey, sliced'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add the pasta and cook for 4 minutes, or until almost tender. Drain.. Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion; cook and stir until tender. Stir in the flour until blended, then gradually stir in the milk so that no lumps form. Season with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and mustard. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture thickens. Remove from the heat and add 2/3 cup cheese and pimento, stirring until cheese melts. Add undrained mushrooms to cheese sauce.. Place a layer of pasta in the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish. Cover with a layer of turkey, and then a layer of cheese sauce. Repeat the layers. Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cup cheese over top.. Bake for about 25 minutes in the preheated oven, until sauce is bubbly and cheese on top is toasted.
